The paper deals with the joint source-channel coding problem in a time-varying MIMO channel with side information, which is a classic problem in information theory and communication engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) channels, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of side information and the block-fading model may also indicate the categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper involves the study of high SNR performance, which may suggest the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
